================================================================================
DISCLAIMER OF LIABILITY
================================================================================

KarmaLego is a research implementation of the KarmaLego temporal pattern
discovery framework, based on academic literature. It is provided as a
general-purpose tool for discovering frequent temporal patterns in time-interval
data and is suitable for research, educational, commercial, and experimental use
across a wide range of domains.

NO WARRANTY IS PROVIDED REGARDING THE ACCURACY, COMPLETENESS, OR SUITABILITY
OF THE SOFTWARE FOR ANY PARTICULAR PURPOSE. THE AUTHORS, CONTRIBUTORS, AND
COPYRIGHT HOLDERS EXPRESSLY DISCLAIM ALL LIABILITY FOR ANY DIRECT, INDIRECT,
INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES (INCLUDING, BUT NOT
LIMITED TO, PROCUREMENT OF SUBSTITUTE GOODS OR SERVICES; LOSS OF USE, DATA,
OR PROFITS; OR BUSINESS INTERRUPTION) ARISING FROM THE USE OF THIS SOFTWARE,
EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES.

Users are solely responsible for validating the correctness and appropriateness
of any results generated by this software for their specific use case, domain,
and applicable legal or regulatory requirements.

================================================================================
THEORETICAL FOUNDATION
================================================================================

This implementation is based on the KarmaLego algorithm described in the
following peer-reviewed publication:

Moskovitch, Robert, and Yuval Shahar. "Temporal Patterns Discovery from
Multivariate Time Series via Temporal Abstraction and Time-Interval Mining."

Users of this software are encouraged to cite this foundational work in any
publications, presentations, or derivative works that utilize this
implementation.

The algorithms, methods, and theoretical framework implemented in this software
are the intellectual property of the original authors of the cited publications.
This software is an independent implementation and is not endorsed or certified
by the original authors unless explicitly stated.